          According to the UN's refugee agency, almost 8Mn Venezuelans have left their homeland since the crisis began in 2014. Credits: AP Photos
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          The US Supreme Court has cleared the way for the Trump administration to end Temporary Protected Status (TPS) for <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-20-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-350-000-venezuelans?source=website" target="_blank">350,000 Venezuelans</a>. TPS allows people from nations experiencing war, natural disasters, or other crises to stay and work legally in the US. This ruling overturns a California court’s decision, temporarily blocking the policy change.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
      Initially, protections for Venezuelans were set to end in October 2026, but the administration has moved that deadline up to April 2025. Since it was an emergency appeal, the justices did not provide a reasoning for the ruling. The sudden shift could abandon many without judicial status, employment, or protection. In August, the Trump administration is also expected to revoke TPS protections for many Haitians.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
       Meanwhile, the administration has launched a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-20-may-25-spotlight-h1-2-voluntary-deportation-program?source=website" target="_blank">“voluntary deportation” program</a>. Under the initiative, the US government flew 68 migrants back to Honduras and Colombia. Each received a $1,000 debit card and was told they may be eligible to apply for judicial reentry. While Trump has promised to ramp up deportations, this program is framed as a softer, more controlled approach.</p>
          </mj-text>
